15:

29:
Like, for example... a local delicacy
known as Tapioca Meteor Heaven
Tea.
34:
What in the world is that?! Did you

37:
I couldn't if I triedâ€”though I've yet to

53:
There's just SO many things to see
and buy in Palpebra! I shouldn't
have expected less from a city of

57:
Next, I think I'd like to experience

61:
I'm curiousâ€”exactly how much
freedom is he to be given in these

63:
I'd say we can let him get some dirt

all, you and I are hereâ€”not to

64:
That being said... it IS His Highness's
first adventure.
70:
Your Highness, let us begin with
something simple. A supply
transport mission.
74:
That sounds perfect! Supplies are
important, after all! Let's make it

78:
Time to make my debut as an
adventurer!
84:
Palpebra is... a more dangerous
place than I thought.
87:
How can such bandits be left to
roam unchecked? I'd heard the
Guild Knights were short of hands,

91:
These bandits are former

days in the Kaleidoscope sent them
down a darker path.
94:
They're no pushovers, either. Among

Knights are simply spread too thin
to handle such a threat.
98:
I see. It must be hard to keep them
all in lineâ€”all those travelers from

Palpebra's struggling to keep the

101:
Yer pretty chipper for someone who
just got taken hostage. Dontcha
know the trouble yer in?
103:
A spoiled little brat like you prolly
ain't never even seen a bandit in the
flesh, 'ave ya? Otherwise you'd be
quakin' in yer boots!
106:
Hmm... Help me understand your
plight. Did the Guild not have
measures in place to help those like
yourselves?
109:
A way to help adventurers down on
their luck by finding them jobs
befitting their skillsâ€”and other
comrades to work alongside?
111:
H-huh. Wouldya look at thatâ€”the
kid's more informed than 'e looks.
Still, I'm asking the questions hereâ€”
113:
Please, hear me out. If we could find
you honest work, would that not
solve your problems?
116:
W-we don't need no stinkin' pity
jobs! Though... Now that I think about
it...
117:
The Guild's system works well
enough, I s'pose... If yer a good little
boy with a squeaky clean record.
Unfortunately, that ain't us.
120: How honest of you to admit that.
123:
I'm thinking what this little
snot-nosed noble needs is a brutal

125:
Folks that don't mince words'll tell

128:
I think I understand. If that rumor
were to spread, it would spell the
end of an adventurer's career.
131:
Such a sullied reputation would
make it harder to build connections
and find allies.
135:
Meritocracy at its purest, for better
or worse...
137:
Even if we wanted to go back to
adventurin', our old crew'd laugh in
our faces. We'd have to resort to
haulin' luggageâ€”a slap in the face,

141:
What if you were to relocateâ€”move
to a land where no one knows you. If
you'd be willing to work, I can

146:
I'd be able to make that happen.
For you see, I am Varen Nialas, fifth
in line to the Farlands' throne!
152:
*sigh*
I wish you hadn't said that.
155:
We've spent more than enough time
here, Your Highness. We should go
before the Guild Knights assume
something's gone wrong.
158:
I am sympathetic to your cause...
That being said, you'll need to come
with usâ€”and we won't take no for an
answer. Isn't that right, Your
Highness?
163:
That's right! Don't worry, this will only
hurt a little.
168:
Swallow Knight support squad,
prepare to move out!
170:
Hey, uh... Just wanted to say thanks.
Fer goin' out of yer way to do this.
173:
Show your appreciation through
your deeds. Work hard, and help
make this venture successfulâ€”it IS
our first time attempting it, after all.
177:
I know we can count on the two of
you!
180:
Yessir! We won't letcha down, Mister
Prince, sir!
183:
That went well. You handled the
negotiations marvelously.
188:
I did, didn't I? Heh. I could get used
to the sound of you praising meâ€”do
it some more!
192:
Your Highness, my constant
approval is not something you need
to seek. You do splendidly without it.
196:
Haha... Is that so? 
No argument there.
200:
And with that, I dare say I'm one
step closer to reforming the Swallow
Knights.
203:
Little by little, step by step, your
actions will better the lives of people
all over the world. I'm sure of it,
Yuwel.
207:
We don't have time to wasteâ€”the
road ahead is long, and there are
many more steps to take!
